To massy_vk from Wisconsin, You can reduce bitterness by blanching most greens in boiling water for 2-3 mins, or you can try any of the following: start the saute with some finely diced bacon/pancetta/linguica, or start it with some carmelized grape tomatoes or shallots to impart the developed sugars, or simply add a little sugar or honey to taste as you cook the greens.

